                         "text":  "# TITLE: How to Apply for a New Residential Water Connection document_id: water-procedure-how-to-apply-for-a-new-residential-water-connection # DOCUMENT_ID:  # VERSION: 1 ## METADATA_BLOCK department:  owner_email: ggg@gmail.com valid_from: 2026-04-16 valid_to: 2027-04-16 locations:  authority_confidence: 0.9 confidence_source:  content_type: procedure service_area: water topic_tags:  related_documents:  prerequisites:  review_cycle: cross_service_flag: false ## CONTENT_BLOCK ### Summary This document explains how to apply for a new residential water connection in Harare, including required documents, fees, and expected timelines. ### StepâbyâStep Instructions 1. Obtain an application form from any Harare City Customer Service Centre (CBD, Mbare, Budiriro, or your zonal office) or download it from the council website. 2. Complete the form and attach certified copies of your National ID and proof of residence (e.g., utility bill, lease agreement not older than 3 months). 3. Submit the form and documents at the nearest customer service centre. You will receive an acknowledgement slip with a reference number. 4. Pay the connection fee (see WATER-FEE-CONNECTION-001) at the cashier. Keep the receipt. 5. A water department inspector will visit your property within 7 working days to verify details and assess the connection point. 6. If approved, a plumber will be scheduled to install the connection. You will be notified of the date via SMS. 7. After installation, the meter will be sealed, and your account will be activated. Your first bill will arrive within 30 days. ### Required Documents - Certified copy of National ID (both sides) - Proof of residence (not older than 3 months) - Completed application form - Payment receipt (after step 4) ### Common Questions Answered - Q: How long does the whole process take? A: Typically 2â4 weeks from submission to activation, depending on inspector availability and weather. - Q: Can I apply online? A: Not yet, but you can download the form online and submit it in person. Online application is planned for 2027. - Q: What if I live in a rented property? A: The landlord\u0027s written consent is required. Contact the water department for a consent form. - Q: Is there a discount for pensioners on the connection fee? A: No, the connection fee is nonâdiscountable. However, pensioners receive a 15% discount on monthly consumption (see WATER-POL-SENIOR-DISCOUNT-001).",
