                         "text":  "# TITLE: WATER-FEE-CONNECTION-001 document_id: water-fee_schedule-water-fee-connection-001 # DOCUMENT_ID:  # VERSION: 1 ## METADATA_BLOCK department:  owner_email: ggg@gmail.com valid_from: 2026-04-17 valid_to: 2027-04-17 locations:  authority_confidence: 0.9 confidence_source:  content_type: fee_schedule service_area: water topic_tags:  related_documents:  prerequisites:  review_cycle: cross_service_flag: false ## CONTENT_BLOCK ### Summary Fees for new residential water connections in Harare. All fees are in Zimbabwean dollars (ZiG) and subject to change without notice. ### Fee Table | Item | Fee (ZiG) | |------|-----------| | Application fee (nonârefundable) | 250 | | Connection fee (standard 15mm meter) | 1,200 | | Meter deposit (refundable after 12 months of good payment) | 800 | | Inspection fee | 350 | | Plumbing works (if required, charged by council plumber) | 500â1,500 (variable) | | Reconnection fee (if disconnected for nonâpayment) | 400 | **Total estimated upfront cost (standard connection, no extra plumbing):** 2,600 ZiG ### Payment Methods - **In person:** Cash or debit card at any Harare City Council cashier (CBD, Mbare, Budiriro, or zonal offices). - **Online:** Pay via the councilâs payment portal (pay.harare.gov.zw) using RTGS or Visa/Mastercard. - **Bank deposit:** CABS account 1002733316 (online payments) or 1003655211 (RTGS). Use your reference number from the application form. ### Common Questions Answered - Q: Is the deposit refundable? A: Yes, after 12 consecutive months of onâtime bill payments, you can request a refund at the water department. - Q: What if I need a larger meter (for a block of flats)? A: Contact the water department for a commercial connection quote. Fees are significantly higher. - Q: Can I pay in instalments? A: No, all fees except the deposit must be paid before installation begins.",
